  <bodyText><![CDATA[<div class="g12">
<div class="white_box_shadow">
<p><img src="/media/13067823/cycling-holidays-in-the-lakes-and-mountains-inghams.jpg" alt="Trulli Houses in Puglia" data-udi="umb://media/3d447fcd145244e793fd64ab0fbc0a40" /></p>
<p><span class="geolocation-title">Puglia, the 'heel' of Italy's boot, is an unspoilt region of olive groves and whitewashed villages that has been overlooked by mass tourism for some time, but is now starting to attract wholly deserved attention. Most famous for its trulli, strange conical roofed houses, Puglia also has magnificent baroque architecture and a beautiful coastline. <br /></span></p>
<p><span class="geolocation-title">DAY 1 </span><br />Fly to Bari and transfer to your hotel before meeting your fellow travellers  and tour manager for a welcome drink.</p>
<p><span class="geolocation-title">DAY 2 <br /></span>This is a day to really soak up the atmosphere of <a data-udi="umb://document/d0c28188245b40a396dd64fb346dffcd" href="/{localLink:umb://document/d0c28188245b40a396dd64fb346dffcd}" title="Puglia">Puglia</a>, with a visit to the whitewashed town of Ostuni followed by a drive through the countryside to taste some of the fine local wines of the region and see the centuries old tradition of olive oil making, for which Puglia is famous. A light lunch is included.</p>
<p><span class="geolocation-title">DAY 3 <br /></span><span>A day dedicated to the nearby towns of the Valle d'Itria, famous for their conical <a data-udi="umb://document/26e2e3f5879445ca92259916b12d82de" href="/{localLink:umb://document/26e2e3f5879445ca92259916b12d82de}" title="Trulli Houses">trulli</a>: Martina Franca, Alberobello and Locorotondo..</span><br /><span><br /><img src="/media/13067823/cycling-holidays-in-the-lakes-and-mountains-inghams.jpg" alt="Otranto in Puglia" data-udi="umb://media/3d447fcd145244e793fd64ab0fbc0a40" /><br /></span><span class="geolocation-title">DAY 4 <br /></span>Enjoy a day at leisure to relax in your hotel or explore the nearby towns.</p>
<p><span><span class="geolocation-title">DAY 5 <br /></span>Today is a full day spent in the region of <a data-udi="umb://document/96d4206678554325862027fe4477f070" href="/{localLink:umb://document/96d4206678554325862027fe4477f070}" title="Puglia &amp; Basilicata">Basilicata</a> and visit the fascinating town of Matera. The Sassi are cave dwellings dating back to prehistoric times but inhabited until quite recently and now a UNESCO World Heritage site.</span></p>
<p><span><span class="geolocation-title">DAY 6<br /></span></span>A full day's excursion to visit the charming seaside town of Otranto with its Norman cathedral. You’ll also enjoy a guided tour of the beautiful little city of Lecce, famous for its flamboyant, baroque architecture.</p>
<span> <img src="/media/13067823/cycling-holidays-in-the-lakes-and-mountains-inghams.jpg" alt="Ostuni in Puglia" data-udi="umb://media/3d447fcd145244e793fd64ab0fbc0a40" /></span><a data-udi="umb://document/61b9b813ca6d419794fd819362771320" href="/{localLink:umb://document/61b9b813ca6d419794fd819362771320}" title="Where to go cycling on an e-bike"><br /></a>
<p><span><span class="geolocation-title">DAY 7<br /></span></span><span>Another day at leisure to relax and unwind and enjoy the hotel's facilities.</span></p>
<p><span><span class="geolocation-title">DAY 8<br /></span></span>Transfer to the airport for your return flight.</p>
</div>
<div class="g6">
<div class="white_box_shadow">
<h2>Tour Includes<br /><br /></h2>
<p>7 nights half board accommodation in a 4 star hotel</p>
<p>Visits to Otranto and Lecce and Ostuni</p>
<p>Full day in Valle d’Itria visiting Alberobello and Locorotondo</p>
<p>Full day to Matera, Basilicata</p>
<p>Wine tasting in Alberobello</p>
</div>
</div>
